## 5 Things to Look for in a Chiller Trucks Supplier in Malaysia

Don’t just look at the price tag. A cheap truck that spends half its life in the workshop is the most expensive truck you’ll ever own. When evaluating suppliers, ask these questions:

### 1. Compressor Brand & Reliability
The compressor is the heart of the truck. Brands like **Thermo King** or **Carrier** are the industry standards for a reason. Ask the supplier which brand they use and, more importantly, if they are authorized service partners for those brands.

### 2. Insulation Quality (The Box)
A good chiller truck isn't just a van with an air conditioner. It’s about the "body" or the "box." High-density polyurethane (PU) foam insulation is essential. If the insulation is thin, your compressor has to work twice as hard, burning more diesel and wearing out faster.

### 3. Customization Options
Every business is different. Do you need a "dual-temperature" truck (one side for chilled, one for frozen)? Do you need a hydraulic tail-lift for heavy crates? A good supplier should be able to customize the body to fit your specific workflow.

### 4. After-Sales Support
Ask about the warranty. Not just on the engine, but on the refrigeration unit. Does the supplier have a 24/7 breakdown team? If your truck breaks down in the middle of the night with RM20,000 worth of frozen prawns inside, you need help *now*, not "next Monday during office hours."

### 5. LHDN & JPJ Compliance
Ensuring the truck meets all Malaysian regulations (Weight limits, APad permits, etc.) is vital. A reputable supplier will handle the documentation or at least guide you through the process so you don't get hit with fines later.

## Financing vs. Outright Purchase: Which is Better for Your SME?

We get it. A brand-new 3-ton chiller truck can easily cost upwards of RM150,000. For a growing Malaysian SME, that’s a lot of cash to tie up in a single asset.

